title: Captain Marvel (2019) - Review
body:
Captain Marvel (2019) – Review

“Higher, further, faster baby.”

Captain Marvel is finally here! Perhaps the most politically-charged film since, well last year’s Black Panther. Ok, so maybe that whole thing has been blown out of proportion. But when you have an extremely vocal group of incels yelling about how Marvel has gone woke, and as a consequence will now be going broke, it can be difficult to remember that there’s a…

summary: I love the difference between how Yon-Rogg treats Carol and how Nick Fury treats her. Yon-Rogg keeps going on about "keeping...
body: I love the difference between how Yon-Rogg treats Carol and how Nick Fury treats her. Yon-Rogg keeps going on about “keeping your emotions in check” (to keep her from using her full power), but Fury just accepts ALL of her almost from the start and he didn’t even know her for as long as Yon did.

reblog.comment: I love the difference between how Yon-Rogg treats Carol and how Nick Fury treats her. Yon-Rogg keeps going on about “keeping your emotions in check” (to keep her from using her full power), but Fury just accepts ALL of her almost from the start and he didn’t even know her for as long as Yon did.

trail.content_raw: I love the difference between how Yon-Rogg treats Carol and how Nick Fury treats her. Yon-Rogg keeps going on about “keeping your emotions in check” (to keep her from using her full power), but Fury just accepts ALL of her almost from the start and he didn’t even know her for as long as Yon did.
trail.content: I love the difference between how Yon-Rogg treats Carol and how Nick Fury treats her. Yon-Rogg keeps going on about “keeping your emotions in check” (to keep her from using her full power), but Fury just accepts ALL of her almost from the start and he didn’t even know her for as long as Yon did.
